OL,3,CMartha's rule is having a
OL,4,Ctransformative effect on patient care
OL,5,Cin the NHS
OL,7,FOne in eight of the 573 calls made to
OL,8,Fraise concerns about a patient's
OL,9,Fcondition deteriorating in September
OL,10,Fand October led to a change in the
OL,11,Fpatient's care, according to NHS
OL,12,FEngland. This could include giving the
OL,13,Fpatients potentially life-saving
OL,14,Fantibiotics, oxygen or other
OL,15,Ftreatments.
OL,17,FAround half of the 573 calls required
OL,18,Fa "clinical review for acute
OL,19,Fdeterioration", according to NHS
OL,20,FEngland figures.
